{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"body":"Live-heal AC assessment: decision_census / binding_walk_complete are emitted only to the gitignored sync-log (not stdout), so heal/acting counts are NOT visible in the GHA run logs (only my baseline_shadow_check RECON line is). The bridge performs breaker-capped heals continuously (max_acting_fraction=0.10; 2026-07-03 census measured ~1.14% acting), so 'capped' is structurally enforced + proven by the offline breaker test (test_reconcile_live_e2e.py::test_blast_radius_breaker_via_classify_api, landed in change 436). The remaining part of the 'capped live heal' AC — a DELIBERATE heal with a bilateral pre-heal backup (Jira JSON + tickets-branch tag, abort-on-backup-failure) and GC-after-grace deletion — is a heavier standalone live operation; sequencing it AFTER the streak/flip/verify chain (the primary rollout) to avoid interfering with the accruing shadow streak on REB. Prioritizing: >=10 clean passes -> flip -> clean flag-ON pass (3 of 4 operational ACs) this session."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783626257004738001,"uuid":"ad6f622f-1b91-4e7a-bc41-853cb883b07f"}